HEADWORD: Brackish
<hw>Brack"ish</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Brack</er> salt water.]</ety> <def>Saltish, or salt in a moderate
degree, as water in saline soil.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Springs in deserts found seem sweet, all <qex>brackish</qex>
though they be.</q> <rj><qau>Byron.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Brackishness</ent>⟦br⟧
